<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/8 (Thu) World population to reach 8 billion / National Palace Museum broken artifacts (Host: Larry)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=678&amp;p=706#p706"><![CDATA[
12/8 (Thu) World population to reach 8 billion / National Palace Museum broken artifacts (Host: Larry)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: World population to reach 8 billion<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.un.org/en/desa/world-population-reach-8-billion-15-november-2022">https://www.un.org/en/desa/world-popula ... ember-2022</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. What is the advantage and disadvantage of having 8 billion people on earth?<br />2. Which do you think is important, the quantity or quality of the population, and why? At present, the acceptance rate of Taiwan’s universities is 98 percent, do you think the overall quality of the nationals has improved, and why?<br />3. Do you think Taiwan’s population is too large or too small at present, and why? What problems can be caused by too much or too little? <br />4. Taiwan has stepped into an elderly society, and the working population is getting smaller. If your physical condition permits, are you willing to <br />postpone your retirement and continue to work? Why?<br /><br />Session 2: National Palace Museum broken artifacts<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4701669">https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4701669</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Do you like to visit museums? Why? What are the benefits of museums?<br />2. What’s the best museum you have ever been to? including in Taiwan or other countries? Why? <br />3. What’s your opinion on the damage to the cultural relics in the national palace museum, including the way the workers handle the artifacts?<br />4. Did you know that the British museum is free to visit, while Taiwan national palace museum costs NT 160 dollars, do you think it’s worth it? Why?<br /><br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sat Dec 03, 2022 3:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
